The article is a transcript of a press briefing by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest, Bill Weldon (CEO for Johnson & Johnson), Rich Lavin (Group President of Caterpillar), and Eric Schmidt (CEO for Google) at the APEC CEO Summit in Hawaii. They discuss the importance of the Asia Pacific region for their businesses, the opportunities for trade and investment, and the need for economic growth and job creation. They also touch on topics such as the North American Leaders Summit, China's currency and trade policies, the impact of the European crisis, and the role of the US in promoting trade and business in Asia.